# Design Document: Vice City Dashboard

## Overview

The Vice City Dashboard is a cyberpunk-themed gaming platform that delivers an immersive, cinematic user experience combining modern web technologies with rich visual effects. This design document outlines the technical architecture, component structure, data models, and implementation strategy for building a high-performance, real-time gaming content platform.

### Core Design Principles

1. **Performance First**: Maintain 60 FPS across all visual effects and animations
2. **Progressive Enhancement**: Graceful degradation for lower-end devices
3. **Real-time by Default**: WebSocket-first architecture for live data
4. **Component Modularity**: Isolated, reusable components with clear interfaces
5. **Accessibility Compliance**: WCAG 2.1 AA standards throughout
6. **Cyberpunk Aesthetic**: Consistent neon, glassmorphism, and futuristic design language

### Technology Stack Summary

**Frontend Framework**: Next.js 15 (App Router) with React 18, TypeScript 5.x
**Styling**: TailwindCSS 4.x with custom neon color palette, CSS-in-JS for dynamic effects
**Animation**: Framer Motion (declarative), GSAP (complex timelines), Lenis (smooth scroll)
**3D Graphics**: Three.js, React Three Fiber, WebGL shaders
**UI Components**: Shadcn UI (base), Aceternity UI (effects), custom cyberpunk components
**State Management**: Zustand (global), React Query (server state), Context API (theme/settings)
**Real-time**: Socket.IO client, WebSocket API
**Backend**: NestJS with GraphQL (Apollo) and REST endpoints
**Database**: PostgreSQL with Prisma ORM
**Caching**: Redis for session, API responses, and real-time data
**Media**: Cloudflare Stream, Bunny CDN, FFmpeg for processing
**Authentication**: Clerk or Auth.js with JWT, OAuth providers (Google, Discord, Steam)
**AI Integration**: OpenAI API or similar for summaries, sentiment analysis, chatbot

## Architecture

### High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Client["Client Layer"]
        Browser[Browser]
        PWA[Service Worker / PWA]
    end
    
    subgraph Frontend["Frontend Application"]
        NextJS[Next.js App Router]
        React[React Components]
        State[State Management]
        WS_Client[WebSocket Client]
    end
    
    subgraph Backend["Backend Services"]
        API[NestJS API Server]
        GraphQL[GraphQL Gateway]
        REST[REST Endpoints]
        WS_Server[WebSocket Server]
        Auth[Auth Service]
    end
    
    subgraph Data["Data Layer"]
        Postgres[(PostgreSQL)]
        Redis[(Redis Cache)]
        CDN[Bunny CDN]
        Stream[Cloudflare Stream]
    end
    
    subgraph External["External Services"]
        OAuth[OAuth Providers]
        AI[AI Services]
        Analytics[Analytics]
    end
    
    Browser --> NextJS
    PWA --> NextJS
    NextJS --> React
    React --> State
    React --> WS_Client
    
    NextJS --> API
    NextJS --> GraphQL
    WS_Client --> WS_Server
    
    API --> REST
    API --> Auth
    GraphQL --> API
    WS_Server --> API
    
    API --> Postgres
    API --> Redis
    API --> CDN
    API --> Stream
    
    Auth --> OAuth
    API --> AI
    API --> Analytics
```

### Frontend Architecture

The frontend follows a layered architecture with clear separation of concerns:

**Presentation Layer**: React components, UI primitives, visual effects
**Business Logic Layer**: Custom hooks, state management, data transformations
**Data Access Layer**: API clients, WebSocket handlers, cache management
**Infrastructure Layer**: Routing, authentication, error boundaries, performance monitoring

### Component Hierarchy

```
App (Root Layout)
├── Providers (Theme, Auth, State, Query)
├── Navigation Sidebar
├── Page Layouts
│   ├── Home Page
│   │   ├── Hero Section
│   │   ├── Live Widgets
│   │   ├── Content Grid
│   │   └── Featured Content
│   ├── News Page
│   │   ├── News Feed
│   │   └── Article Detail
│   ├── Videos Page
│   │   ├── Video Grid
│   │   ├── Video Player
│   │   └── Watch Party
│   ├── Events Page
│   │   ├── Event List
│   │   └── Event Detail
│   ├── Stats Page
│   │   └── Statistics Dashboard
│   ├── Community Page
│   │   ├── Chat System
│   │   └── Community Metrics
│   └── Settings Page
├── Visual Effects Layer
│   ├── Mouse Reactive Glow
│   ├── Particle System
│   ├── Weather Effects
│   ├── VHS Glitch
│   └── CRT Effect
└── Audio Engine
```

### Backend Architecture

The backend uses a modular NestJS architecture:

**API Gateway**: Routes requests to appropriate services
**Authentication Module**: JWT validation, OAuth integration, session management
**Content Module**: CRUD operations for articles, videos, events, characters
**Real-time Module**: WebSocket event handling, room management, synchronization
**Media Module**: Video processing, CDN integration, streaming
**Analytics Module**: Event tracking, metrics aggregation
**AI Module**: Integration with AI services for summaries, sentiment, chatbot

### Data Flow Patterns

**Static Content Flow**:
1. Client requests page → Next.js SSR/SSG
2. Server fetches data from API/Database
3. Server renders HTML with initial data
4. Client hydrates and becomes interactive

**Real-time Data Flow**:
1. Client establishes WebSocket connection
2. Server authenticates and assigns to rooms
3. Server broadcasts events to subscribed clients
4. Client updates UI reactively

**Media Streaming Flow**:
1. Client requests video → API returns CDN URL
2. Client fetches video from CDN with adaptive bitrate
3. Client reports playback metrics to API
4. API updates analytics and viewer counts

## Components and Interfaces

### Core Components

#### 1. Navigation Sidebar Component

**Purpose**: Persistent navigation menu with neon styling and active state management

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface NavigationSidebarProps {
  isCollapsed?: boolean;
  onNavigate?: (path: string) => void;
  activeRoute: string;
}
```

**State**:
- `isOpen`: boolean (mobile menu state)
- `hoveredItem`: string | null

**Key Methods**:
- `handleNavigation(path: string)`: Navigate to route and update active state
- `toggleMobile()`: Toggle mobile menu visibility

**Dependencies**: Next.js router, Framer Motion for animations

---

#### 2. Hero Section Component

**Purpose**: Cinematic hero section with video background and animated title

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface HeroSectionProps {
  title: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  backgroundVideo?: string;
  backgroundImage?: string;
  ctaButtons: Array<{
    label: string;
    href: string;
    variant: 'primary' | 'secondary';
  }>;
  onCtaClick?: (href: string) => void;
}
```

**State**:
- `isVideoLoaded`: boolean
- `isVisible`: boolean (for scroll animations)

**Key Methods**:
- `handleVideoLoad()`: Set video loaded state
- `handleCtaClick(href: string)`: Handle CTA button clicks

**Dependencies**: Framer Motion, video element API

---

#### 3. Content Card Component

**Purpose**: Reusable card for displaying content with glassmorphism and hover effects

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface ContentCardProps {
  id: string;
  type: 'article' | 'video' | 'gallery' | 'character' | 'event';
  thumbnail: string;
  title: string;
  metadata: {
    date?: string;
    category?: string;
    duration?: string;
    author?: string;
  };
  onClick?: (id: string) => void;
  variant?: 'default' | 'hologram';
}
```

**State**:
- `isHovered`: boolean
- `isImageLoaded`: boolean
- `mousePosition`: { x: number; y: number }

**Key Methods**:
- `handleMouseMove(e: MouseEvent)`: Track mouse for 3D tilt effect
- `handleClick()`: Navigate to detail view
- `handleImageLoad()`: Set image loaded state

**Dependencies**: Framer Motion, Intersection Observer for lazy loading

---

#### 4. Live Widget Component

**Purpose**: Real-time data display with animated value updates

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface LiveWidgetProps {
  type: 'viewer-count' | 'countdown' | 'community-pulse' | 'social-stats';
  title: string;
  value: number | string;
  icon?: React.ReactNode;
  updateInterval?: number;
}
```

**State**:
- `currentValue`: number | string
- `previousValue`: number | string
- `isConnected`: boolean

**Key Methods**:
- `updateValue(newValue: number | string)`: Animate value transition
- `formatValue(value: number)`: Format numbers with separators

**Dependencies**: WebSocket client, Framer Motion for value animations

---

#### 5. Chat System Component

**Purpose**: Real-time chat with message display and input

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface ChatSystemProps {
  roomId: string;
  userId: string;
  username: string;
  maxMessages?: number;
  onMessageSent?: (message: string) => void;
}
```

**State**:
- `messages`: Array<Message>
- `inputValue`: string
- `isConnected`: boolean
- `onlineUsers`: Array<User>

**Key Methods**:
- `sendMessage(content: string)`: Send message via WebSocket
- `handleIncomingMessage(message: Message)`: Add message to list
- `scrollToBottom()`: Auto-scroll to latest message

**Dependencies**: Socket.IO client, message validation

---

#### 6. Video Player Component

**Purpose**: Custom video player with controls and adaptive streaming

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface VideoPlayerProps {
  src: string;
  poster?: string;
  autoplay?: boolean;
  controls?: boolean;
  onPlay?: () => void;
  onPause?: () => void;
  onTimeUpdate?: (currentTime: number) => void;
  watchPartyMode?: boolean;
  watchPartyId?: string;
}
```

**State**:
- `isPlaying`: boolean
- `currentTime`: number
- `duration`: number
- `volume`: number
- `quality`: string
- `isFullscreen`: boolean
- `isSyncing`: boolean (watch party)

**Key Methods**:
- `play()`: Start playback
- `pause()`: Pause playback
- `seek(time: number)`: Seek to timestamp
- `setQuality(quality: string)`: Change video quality
- `syncWithHost(hostTime: number)`: Sync playback in watch party

**Dependencies**: HLS.js for adaptive streaming, Fullscreen API, WebSocket for watch party sync

---

#### 7. Particle System Component

**Purpose**: Animated background particles with performance optimization

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface ParticleSystemProps {
  particleCount?: number;
  colors?: string[];
  speed?: number;
  enabled?: boolean;
  performanceMode?: boolean;
}
```

**State**:
- `particles`: Array<Particle>
- `animationFrame`: number | null
- `canvasContext`: CanvasRenderingContext2D | null

**Key Methods**:
- `initParticles()`: Generate particle array
- `updateParticles()`: Update particle positions
- `renderParticles()`: Draw particles to canvas
- `startAnimation()`: Begin animation loop
- `stopAnimation()`: Stop animation loop

**Dependencies**: Canvas API, requestAnimationFrame

---

#### 8. Mouse Reactive Glow Component

**Purpose**: Cursor-following glow effect with smooth easing

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface MouseReactiveGlowProps {
  radius?: number;
  colors?: string[];
  intensity?: number;
  enabled?: boolean;
}
```

**State**:
- `mousePosition`: { x: number; y: number }
- `targetPosition`: { x: number; y: number }

**Key Methods**:
- `handleMouseMove(e: MouseEvent)`: Update target position
- `updateGlowPosition()`: Ease glow to target with animation frame
- `renderGlow()`: Update DOM element position

**Dependencies**: requestAnimationFrame, CSS blend modes

---

#### 9. Neon Glow Engine

**Purpose**: Centralized system for applying neon glow effects to elements

**Interface**:
```typescript
interface NeonGlowEngine {
  applyGlow(element: HTMLElement, color: string, intensity: number): void;
  removeGlow(element: HTMLElement): void;
  pulseGlow(element: HTMLElement, duration: number): void;
  registerElement(element: HTMLElement, config: GlowConfig): void;
}

interface GlowConfig {
  color: string;
  intensity: number;
  hoverIntensity?: number;
  pulseInterval?: number;
}
```

**Key Methods**:
- `applyGlow()`: Add glow effect to element
- `removeGlow()`: Remove glow effect
- `pulseGlow()`: Animate pulsing glow
- `registerElement()`: Auto-manage glow for element lifecycle

**Dependencies**: CSS custom properties, GSAP for animations

---

#### 10. Audio Engine Component

**Purpose**: Manage ambient soundtrack and UI sound effects

**Interface**:
```typescript
interface AudioEngine {
  playAmbient(trackUrl: string): void;
  stopAmbient(): void;
  setVolume(volume: number): void;
  playSound(soundId: string): void;
  mute(): void;
  unmute(): void;
  fadeIn(duration: number): void;
  fadeOut(duration: number): void;
}
```

**State**:
- `ambientTrack`: HTMLAudioElement | null
- `volume`: number
- `isMuted`: boolean
- `soundEffects`: Map<string, HTMLAudioElement>

**Key Methods**:
- `playAmbient()`: Start ambient soundtrack with loop
- `playSound()`: Play UI sound effect
- `setVolume()`: Adjust volume with fade
- `fadeIn()/fadeOut()`: Smooth volume transitions

**Dependencies**: Web Audio API, audio element API

---

#### 11. Configuration Parser

**Purpose**: Parse and validate dashboard configuration files

**Interface**:
```typescript
interface ConfigurationParser {
  parse(input: string, format: 'json' | 'yaml'): Result<Configuration, ParseError>;
  validate(config: Configuration): Result<Configuration, ValidationError>;
  prettyPrint(config: Configuration, format: 'json' | 'yaml'): string;
}

interface Configuration {
  apiEndpoint: string;
  wsEndpoint: string;
  cdnUrl: string;
  features: {
    ai: boolean;
    chat: boolean;
    watchParty: boolean;
    weather: boolean;
    particles: boolean;
    vhsGlitch: boolean;
    crtEffect: boolean;
  };
  theme: {
    primaryColor: string;
    accentColor: string;
    glowIntensity: number;
  };
  performance: {
    targetFPS: number;
    particleCount: number;
    enableGPU: boolean;
  };
}

interface ParseError {
  line: number;
  column: number;
  message: string;
}

interface ValidationError {
  field: string;
  message: string;
}
```

**Key Methods**:
- `parse()`: Parse configuration string to object
- `validate()`: Validate configuration against schema
- `prettyPrint()`: Format configuration object to string
- `applyDefaults()`: Apply default values for optional fields

**Dependencies**: JSON parser, YAML parser (js-yaml), Zod for validation

---

### API Interfaces

#### REST API Endpoints

**Content Endpoints**:
- `GET /api/articles` - List articles with pagination
- `GET /api/articles/:id` - Get article details
- `GET /api/videos` - List videos with pagination
- `GET /api/videos/:id` - Get video details
- `GET /api/events` - List events with filters
- `GET /api/events/:id` - Get event details
- `GET /api/characters` - List characters
- `GET /api/characters/:id` - Get character details
- `GET /api/gallery` - List gallery items

**User Endpoints**:
- `POST /api/auth/register` - Register new user
- `POST /api/auth/login` - Login user
- `POST /api/auth/logout` - Logout user
- `GET /api/auth/me` - Get current user
- `PUT /api/users/:id` - Update user profile
- `GET /api/users/:id/preferences` - Get user preferences
- `PUT /api/users/:id/preferences` - Update user preferences

**Community Endpoints**:
- `POST /api/comments` - Create comment
- `GET /api/comments/:contentId` - Get comments for content
- `POST /api/comments/:id/react` - Add reaction to comment
- `GET /api/community/metrics` - Get community metrics

**Analytics Endpoints**:
- `POST /api/analytics/event` - Track analytics event
- `GET /api/stats` - Get dashboard statistics

#### GraphQL Schema

```graphql
type Query {
  articles(limit: Int, offset: Int, category: String): ArticleConnection!
  article(id: ID!): Article
  videos(limit: Int, offset: Int): VideoConnection!
  video(id: ID!): Video
  events(filter: EventFilter): [Event!]!
  event(id: ID!): Event
  characters(game: String): [Character!]!
  character(id: ID!): Character
  search(query: String!, types: [ContentType!]): SearchResults!
  communityMetrics: CommunityMetrics!
  statistics(timeRange: TimeRange!): Statistics!
}

type Mutation {
  createComment(input: CreateCommentInput!): Comment!
  reactToComment(commentId: ID!, reaction: ReactionType!): Comment!
  registerForEvent(eventId: ID!): EventRegistration!
  createWatchParty(videoId: ID!): WatchParty!
  joinWatchParty(partyId: ID!): WatchParty!
  updatePreferences(input: PreferencesInput!): UserPreferences!
}

type Subscription {
  messageAdded(roomId: ID!): Message!
  viewerCountUpdated: ViewerCount!
  eventStarting(eventId: ID!): Event!
  watchPartySync(partyId: ID!): PlaybackState!
}
```

#### WebSocket Events

**Client → Server**:
- `chat:join` - Join chat room
- `chat:leave` - Leave chat room
- `chat:message` - Send chat message
- `watchparty:join` - Join watch party
- `watchparty:sync` - Send playback state
- `presence:update` - Update user presence

**Server → Client**:
- `chat:message` - Receive chat message
- `chat:user_joined` - User joined room
- `chat:user_left` - User left room
- `watchparty:sync` - Receive playback state
- `metrics:update` - Live metrics update
- `event:starting` - Event starting notification
- `presence:update` - User presence update

## Data Models

### Frontend Data Models

#### User Model
```typescript
interface User {
  id: string;
  username: string;
  email: string;
  avatar?: string;
  role: 'user' | 'admin' | 'moderator';
  reputation: number;
  createdAt: Date;
  preferences: UserPreferences;
}

interface UserPreferences {
  theme: 'pink' | 'blue' | 'purple';
  audioVolume: number;
  audioMuted: boolean;
  visualEffects: {
    particles: boolean;
    mouseGlow: boolean;
    weather: boolean;
    vhsGlitch: boolean;
    crtEffect: boolean;
  };
  performanceMode: boolean;
  notifications: {
    events: boolean;
    community: boolean;
    updates: boolean;
  };
}
```

#### Content Models
```typescript
interface Article {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  slug: string;
  excerpt: string;
  content: string;
  thumbnail: string;
  author: User;
  category: string;
  publishedAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
  tags: string[];
  aiSummary?: string;
}

interface Video {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  slug: string;
  description: string;
  thumbnail: string;
  videoUrl: string;
  duration: number;
  category: string;
  publishedAt: Date;
  viewCount: number;
  qualities: VideoQuality[];
}

interface VideoQuality {
  label: string;
  url: string;
  bitrate: number;
  resolution: string;
}

interface Event {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  thumbnail: string;
  startDate: Date;
  endDate?: Date;
  category: 'launch' | 'tournament' | 'announcement' | 'update';
  isLive: boolean;
  registeredUsers: number;
  maxParticipants?: number;
}

interface Character {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  game: string;
  role: string;
  thumbnail: string;
  description: string;
  attributes: {
    class?: string;
    abilities?: string[];
    stats?: Record<string, number>;
  };
  model3dUrl?: string;
  popularity: number;
}

interface GalleryItem {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  imageUrl: string;
  thumbnailUrl: string;
  game: string;
  category: string;
  resolution: string;
  uploadedAt: Date;
}
```

#### Real-time Models
```typescript
interface Message {
  id: string;
  roomId: string;
  userId: string;
  username: string;
  content: string;
  timestamp: Date;
  avatar?: string;
}

interface WatchParty {
  id: string;
  videoId: string;
  hostId: string;
  participants: PartyParticipant[];
  playbackState: PlaybackState;
  createdAt: Date;
}

interface PartyParticipant {
  userId: string;
  username: string;
  avatar?: string;
  joinedAt: Date;
}

interface PlaybackState {
  isPlaying: boolean;
  currentTime: number;
  timestamp: Date;
}

interface LiveMetrics {
  viewerCount: number;
  activeUsers: number;
  communityPulse: number;
  trendingTopics: string[];
  sentiment: number;
}
```

#### Visual Effect Models
```typescript
interface Particle {
  id: string;
  x: number;
  y: number;
  vx: number;
  vy: number;
  size: number;
  color: string;
  opacity: number;
}

interface GlowConfig {
  color: string;
  intensity: number;
  radius: number;
  blur: number;
}
```

### Database Schema (PostgreSQL)

```sql
-- Users table
CREATE TABLE users (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  username VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  password_hash VARCHAR(255),
  avatar_url TEXT,
  role VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'user',
  reputation INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- User preferences table
CREATE TABLE user_preferences (
  user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  theme VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'pink',
  audio_volume DECIMAL(3,2) DEFAULT 0.30,
  audio_muted BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  visual_effects JSONB DEFAULT '{}',
  performance_mode BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  notifications JSONB DEFAULT '{}',
  updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Articles table
CREATE TABLE articles (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  slug VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  excerpt TEXT,
  content TEXT NOT NULL,
  thumbnail_url TEXT,
  author_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  category VARCHAR(50),
  published_at TIMESTAMP,
  updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  tags TEXT[],
  ai_summary TEXT,
  view_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0
);

-- Videos table
CREATE TABLE videos (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  slug VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  thumbnail_url TEXT,
  video_url TEXT NOT NULL,
  duration INTEGER,
  category VARCHAR(50),
  published_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  view_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  qualities JSONB DEFAULT '[]'
);

-- Events table
CREATE TABLE events (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  thumbnail_url TEXT,
  start_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  end_date TIMESTAMP,
  category VARCHAR(50),
  is_live BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  max_participants INTEGER,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Event registrations table
CREATE TABLE event_registrations (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  event_id UUID REFERENCES events(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  registered_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  UNIQUE(event_id, user_id)
);

-- Characters table
CREATE TABLE characters (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  game VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  role VARCHAR(100),
  thumbnail_url TEXT,
  description TEXT,
  attributes JSONB DEFAULT '{}',
  model_3d_url TEXT,
  popularity INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Gallery items table
CREATE TABLE gallery_items (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  title VARCHAR(255),
  image_url TEXT NOT NULL,
  thumbnail_url TEXT,
  game VARCHAR(255),
  category VARCHAR(50),
